Description: Vintage tint Warmoth solid mahogany flat double-cut LP. Well loved and used. Numerous dents, dings, and scratches. There are two holes in the front (see pictures). The pinhole is repaired with wood from behind. A custom tortoise pickguard covers the "tunnel". Seymour Duncan mini-humbuckers (routed for P90's). Varitone circuit by Kellingsound. Hipshot bridge and Locking Tuners. The neck has some discoloration due to use. It has a thin satin finish. Neck straight and truss rod works as it should. Frets are like new. A sweet player with low action. New SKB polyfoam case included. All pots are A500k. The master volume has a treble bleed circuit. The varitone is 6 way. The caps are .0022, .0047, .0068, .022, .047 and .15 These all run through a 2.6h choke. The volume for the varitone is converted to be noload so when it's turned all the way up it bypasses the entire tone circuit. You can feel a notch when you turn it up so you know it's in bypass. The varitone has a volume control so you can blend in how much of the tone you want from the varitone switch. The pot behind the master volume is a bass cut. This works well when playing with lots of distortion and saturation to clean up your tone for leads. You can also combine this pot with the varitone to give you tons of tone combinations.
